Version 1 Rules

The configs/ folder is the only source of static gameplay configuration.

Every configuration file is loaded through ConfigLoader.

Managers and subsystems must not hardcode configurable gameplay values.

Configuration files contain data only and never executable logic.

tiles.json is the only source of tile metadata.

levels.json is the only source of level definitions.

powerups.json is the only source of powerup definitions.

obstacles.json is the only source of obstacle definitions.

rewards.json is the only source of reward tables.

economy.json is the only source of economy balancing values.

story.json contains story metadata only; dialogue content resides in the stories/ folder.

Configuration files may reference assets, resources, and scenes by path but never load them directly.

The Config System depends on no gameplay subsystem; gameplay subsystems depend on it through ConfigLoader.

